article.headline: E. Michigan 56, Ball St. 52
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Jesse Bunkley scored 22 points on 7-of-14 shooting to lead Eastern Michigan to a 56-52 victory over Ball State on Saturday. Bunkley made three 3-pointers during a 13-3 Eastern Michigan run in the first half as the Eagles (7-9, 2-1 Mid-American Conference) built their lead to 10 points with 3:34 remaining in the first half. Eastern Michigan led 29-18 at halftime and never trailed in the second half. Ahmaad Cook came off the bench to hit five 3-pointers and lead Ball State (4-12, 0-3) with 17 points. Micah Rollin added 13 points and five rebounds for the Cardinals. The Ball State bench outscored the Eastern Michigan reserves 31-10 in the Cardinals' sixth straight loss.
